<div class="container my-5">

  <div class="row g-5 my-4 d-flex align-items-center">
    <div class="col-md-7">
      <h2>Coverage</h2>
      <p>News serves as a crucial mechanism for keeping the public informed about current events and important developments. It encompasses a broad range of topics, including politics, economics, science, technology, culture, and more. News outlets, whether traditional newspapers, television channels, or digital platforms, strive to provide accurate and timely information to help individuals stay informed about the world around them.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-5">
      <img class="img-fluid rounded shadow-sm" src="https://i.ibb.co/dQ0RgfH/images-2.jpg" alt="News Coverage">
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="row g-5 my-4 d-flex align-items-center">
    <div class="col-md-7 order-md-2">
      <h2>Dispatches</h2>
      <p>The evolution of news media has been marked by significant changes in how information is delivered and consumed. The rise of digital platforms and social media has transformed the landscape, allowing for real-time updates and a more interactive experience. While this shift has made news more accessible, it has also introduced challenges related to the credibility of sources and the spread of misinformation. As a result, critical thinking and media literacy have become essential skills for navigating the modern news environment.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-5 order-md-1">
      <img class="img-fluid rounded shadow-sm" src="https://i.ibb.co/sVRRDX9/download.png" alt="News Dispatches">
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="row g-5 my-4 d-flex align-items-center">
    <div class="col-md-7">
      <h2>Reports</h2>
      <p>In addition to reporting facts, news organizations often play a role in shaping public opinion and influencing policy decisions. Through investigative journalism and in-depth reporting, the media can highlight issues that might otherwise go unnoticed, prompting discussions and actions that address societal concerns. The balance between reporting news impartially and engaging in advocacy or commentary is an ongoing debate within the field, reflecting the complex nature of media's role in democratic societies.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-5">
      <img class="img-fluid rounded shadow-sm" src="https://i.ibb.co/51dxN4k/image1.jpg" alt="News Reports">
    </div>
  </div>
  
